de\_interruption\_beta
--------------------


Theme:

Counter-Terrorists have transported a number of weaponry and ammunition to a port-side warehouse for distribution. The information was leaked to a group of Terrorists who plans to interrupt the transfer and destroy the goods. Some rare and expensive medicine were also awaiting transport at the scene and became an additional target. 

-------------

This is the third map (second to be publicly released) I have created.

In this map I have examined the use of a night environment, different light styles, and map fog for the first time.

Map comes with NAV (no places names in beta), and level overview / radar overview.


As always, feedback and comments much appreciated. =)

First attempt on making a map.

Story:

The Terrorists are transporting/selling guns, bombs, and private information from an abandoned factory for many dangerous groups and criminal organizations.
The FBI managed to track them down to the exact location of the HQ, the terrorist mission now is to blow up the building in order to cover their tracks.

---
You (as the Counter Terrorist) must:

Invade the building through the main gate or the side door leading to site B.
Stop the Terrorists from destroying the factory with all the evidences of their crimes and information of their clients.

---
You (as the Terrorist) must:

Plant the C4 at A to destroy all computers with useful information to slow down future tracking.
Plant the C4 at B to destroy stolen bombs, killing FBI agents in the process.

Industrial Complex - Bomb-Defuse

from bombing weapon crates.

C4 must destroy targets.

targets in the mission.

Credits : Created by Warhawk3407 - July 2011

Notes
------------------
The map still based on my previous map, dm\_industrial\_final, but I've rebuilt one area (BombA) and created a new one (BombB). The gameplay is balanced but T have to be aggressive to win. All files are packed in the BSP. **The nav file is complete**, bots are able to walk everywhere and I added place names.
